'''潘公凯'''（{{lang-en|Philip P. Pan}}）是一位[[美国|美国]]记者、作家。

==生平==
他曾任[[華盛頓郵報|華盛頓郵報]]北京分社社長，[[紐約時報|紐約時報]]國際新聞版主任助理，紐約時報北京分社社長。<ref>[http://www.worldjournal.com/1023760/article-%E7%B4%90%E6%99%822%E8%A8%98%E8%80%85%E7%B0%BD%E8%AD%89%E8%A2%AB%E6%8B%96%E5%BB%B6/ 紐時2記者簽證被拖延]{{dead link|date=2018年3月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>

他凭借记述[[中华人民共和国政治|中国现代政治变迁]]的《[[走出毛的影子：为新中国的灵魂奋斗|走出毛的影子：为新中国的灵魂奋斗]]》一书获得了2009年{{link-en|亚瑟罗斯图书奖|Arthur Ross Book Award}}金奖。此书也被《[[华盛顿邮报|华盛顿邮报]]》和《[[经济学人|经济学人]]》杂志评为2008年最佳图书之一。《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》文学评论员[[角谷美智子|角谷美智子]]评价此书有“第一手报道的即时性和小说领域的情感深度。<ref>{{cite web  |url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/discussion/2008/07/01/DI2008070102553.html    |title=Books: 'Out of Mao's Shadow'  |accessdate=2012-03-23|archive-date=2019-06-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190603003839/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/discussion/2008/07/01/DI2008070102553.html  |dead-url=no  }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.slate.com/id/2195904/|title=The Party vs. the People|accessdate=2012-03-23|archive-date=2011-02-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110216144502/http://www.slate.com/id/2195904|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.charlierose.com/guest/view/6430 |title=Philip Pan |accessdate=2012-03-23 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120620011052/http://www.charlierose.com/guest/view/6430 |archivedate=2012-06-20 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pbs.org/moyers/journal/08222008/profile2.html|title=Philip Pan|accessdate=2012-03-23|archive-date=2020-08-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200806073454/https://www.pbs.org/moyers/journal/08222008/profile2.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.pbs.org/moyers/journal/08222008/profile2.html |title=Philip Pan |accessdate=2012-03-23 |archive-date=2020-08-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200806073454/https://www.pbs.org/moyers/journal/08222008/profile2.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2008/07/15/books/15kaku.html|title=Dispatches From Capitalist China|accessdate=2012-03-23|archive-date=2020-11-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201127111844/https://www.nytimes.com/2008/07/15/books/15kaku.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>2013年任《纽约时报》驻北京分社社长，3月向中国当局提出申请，未获批准。<ref>{{cite news |title=《纽约时报》一名驻华记者被迫离境 |url=https://cn.nytimes.com/china/20130101/c01reporter/ |accessdate=2018-12-26 |agency=纽约时报 |date=2013年1月1日 |archive-date=2020-11-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201129230210/https://cn.nytimes.com/china/20130101/c01reporter/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>潘公凯后参与开设纽约时报中文版。

